If you write a function that could fail (like logging into an account), you don't return a simple string. You return a `Result`!

```rust
fn open_file(path: &str) -> Result<String, String> {
    if path == "secret.txt" {
        Ok(String::from("File data here"))
    } else {
        Err(String::from("File not found!"))
    }
}
```
